text.section:
Notwithstanding any other provision of law to the contrary, the Transportation Cabinet shall upon request furnish full information regarding the commercial driving history record of any person to the following:
The driver licensing administrator, court official, or police agency of this or any other state or foreign jurisdiction, requesting that information;
Any employer or prospective employer;
The commercial driver; or
Any other person so established by administrative regulation, pursuant to KRS Chapter 13A, of the cabinet.
